Moreover, the segmentation of the market based on application highlights the significance of international airports in driving market demand. With higher footfall and a diverse range of passengers passing through international airports, the need for resting facilities, including sleeping pods, is more pronounced. This segment is expected to be a key revenue generator for market players, as they seek to capitalize on the growing demand for innovative and comfortable solutions for travelers. Additionally, the segmentation by airport capacity underscores the opportunity for large size airports to enhance their passenger experience through the provision of high-quality sleeping accommodations.

